Intensity arc:     {{ intensity_arc }} (arc peaks in the middle then falls — no violence)

{{ speakers_block(speakers) }}
SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
This is a hard-negative confusor: the argument is loud and emotional but resolves peacefully.
  1. Trigger — one partner raises a grievance about the argument topic.
  2. Counter — the other partner defends themselves or counter-accuses.
  3. Escalation — voices rise; both speakers are frustrated and speak over each other.
  4. Turning point — one speaker says something that diffuses the tension (apology, humour, insight).
  5. Resolution — the couple moves toward a genuine (if imperfect) resolution or truce.
IMPORTANT: this clip must NOT contain threats, coercion, or physical violence. It is
deliberately designed to challenge classifiers that rely only on acoustic energy.

